  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This package evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all 13 credibility factors. The intended use scope — predicting NIH index for a 5 L/min, 120 mmHg operating point in a Class III implantable VAD — is described in the Claim and Requirement prose. All seven assessed factors meet or exceed required gradation levels at MRL 5; six factors are scoped out as not applicable to the current submission boundary. Decision: Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-predicts-absolute-nih-index-class3",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v2",
